data.description: Just a short walk along sidewalk going down 9th St to the public park with biking & walking paved path around most Lake Wailes Lake- - .  Also the public boat ramp is in this area. Close to everything - - - original downtown Lake Wales with its unique shops & Saturdays Farmers Market is only 1+ mile away.  Bok Tower, one of the finest & most unique attractions in all of Florida is only 2 miles N. Public schools & the Lake Wales Hospital are very near.  All the shopping you normally need can be found in downtown Lake Wales or along Hwy 60 a few miles to the S. or along Hwy U.S. 27 a few miles to the N.  Master BR in this home is huge with a large master bath including double sinks, shower & separate tub along with a very large walk-in closet. The enclosed porch (not included in living space) is really finished to the degree of living space with tile floors & glass windows looking out to the huge back yard that has a variety of tropical fruit trees planted.  The den could easily be converted to a 4th BR - -  don't miss this opportunity to join the Lake Wales Community in such a great location!!
